FBIS3-1440 "drafr060_d_94006" FBIS-AFR-94-060 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Mar 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Angola Wrapup of UNITA Radio Reports, Clashes, Activities UNITA, MPLA Suspend Talks in Lusaka LD2803190294 Lisbon RTP Internacional Television in Portuguese 1800 GMT 28 Mar 94 LD2803190294 Lisbon RTP Internacional Television Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Text] UNITA [National Union for the Total Independence of Angola] and the MPLA [Popular Movement for the Liberation of Angola] have suspended their talks in Lusaka. According to a source at the talks, the measure was taken to avoid a total break down in the negotiations between the two sides. There is disagreement on five fundamental points and, to avoid a break down, they have suspended the negotiations.
